Start=Dot
Dot, another mini-framework experiment for Ruby and Rack

==Example

In a file called my_app.rb, put the following

	require 'dot'

	class MyApp
  
	  include Dot::App
  
	  map '', :			index
	  map 'status', 	:type
  
	  def index
	    'My app has action!'
	  end
  
	  def status
	    throw(:halt, :status=>500, :body=>'type param required!') unless @request.params['type']
		"Status for #{@request.params['type]}..."
	  end
  
	end

Go to the directory where you saved your my_app.rb file.

Create a config.ru file like:
	
	require 'my_app.rb'
	run MyApp.new

Start the server:
	
	rackup

Now "browse" to:
	
	http://localhost:9292/
	http://localhost:9292/status?type=txn
	http://localhost:9292/status

Say, "wow, big deal". Or, hey now I an create mini-ruby web apps with relative ease!

